From: Michael Froman <mfroman@mozilla.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 10:19:53 -0500
Subject: (tmp-cherry-pick) Revert "Refactor RTCStatsCollector to have a
 CollectionContext" (203586147d)

This reverts commit 46e36dc84a80dc0c5955824046dce688b1448dcb.

Reason for revert: Causes crashes.

Original change's description:
> Refactor RTCStatsCollector to have a CollectionContext
>
> Encapsulates state variables used during a stats gathering session into
> a new internal `CollectionContext` struct. Previously, these variables
> were stored as member variables of `RTCStatsCollector`, despite
> implicitly having a shorter lifecycle, associated with the stats
> gathering operation (only being valid for the duration of an
> asynchronous getStats call).
>
> This change makes further improvements to remove blocking calls simpler.
>
> Bug: webrtc:42222804
> Change-Id: I98b2a0f408138d5a65afcee0da8a37eea0cc37bb
> Reviewed-on: https://webrtc-review.googlesource.com/c/src/+/443380
> Reviewed-by: Harald Alvestrand <hta@webrtc.org>
> Commit-Queue: Tomas Gunnarsson <tommi@webrtc.org>
